### 17. PRESCRIPTION FOR OP AND DISCHARGE

Extract prescription with medication details (name with strength, form if mentioned, morning/noon/evening/night quantities, duration, timing, remarks). For Discharge cases, these are medications to be followed upon discharge. If the form (tablet, syrup, capsule, drops, injection, etc.) is mentioned or clearly implied, include it in the "form" field. If not mentioned, omit or leave empty.

**Extraction Rules***
✅ **durationDays MUST be a number in days**: Convert all durations to days.                                                                                                          
    "1 month" → "30", "2 weeks" → "14", "3 months" → "90", "1 year" → "365", "6 weeks" → "42".                                                                                            
    If doctor says "continue" or "lifelong", or doesn''t mention, use "".
 ✅ **SOS / PRN / As-needed medicines**: When doctor says "if needed", "when required", "SOS", "PRN", or equivalent in other languages (Tamil: "thevaipadda/தேவைப்பட்டா", Hindi: "zaroorat padne par", Telugu: "avasaramaithe"):
     - Set morning_qty/noon_qty/evening_qty/night_qty all to "0"
     - Put "SOS" or "As needed" in the remarks field along with the condition
       (e.g., "SOS - take if fever above 100°F", "As needed for pain")
     - ❌ Do NOT treat "if needed" / "thevaipattaa" as a medicine name — it is an instruction qualifier
✅ **"Continue current medicines"**: When doctor reviews the patient''s current medications                                                                                              
     and says "continue", "same medicines", "continue all":                                                                                                                               
     - Extract EACH medicine individually into the prescription with full details                                                                                                         
     - These medicines should appear in BOTH current_medications (History) AND prescription                                                                                               
     - Do NOT output "continue current medicines" as a prescription entry — list actual names
✅ **Patient-mentioned meds the doctor doesn''t address**: If the patient mentions taking
     medications on their own ("I''m on BP tablets", "she''s been taking pain meds") but the
     doctor does NOT say "continue", "same medicines", or otherwise prescribe/modify them
     in this visit, do NOT include them in prescription. They belong in HISTORY only.
✅ **No vague placeholders**: If the doctor says "I''ll prescribe tablets for 3 months",
     "give him pain meds", or any equivalent without naming a specific drug, return an
     EMPTY array []. Do NOT invent a name like "Tablets for pain management" or "Pain
     medication". The doctor will write the actual prescription on paper.

***Example:***
```
json
{
  "prescription": [
    {
      "name": "Paracetamol 500mg",
      "form": "Tablet",
      "remarks": "Take after food",
      "morning_qty": "1",
      "noon_qty": "0",
      "evening_qty": "1",
