### 15. DISCUSSION AND CONSENT RADIOLOGY

Extract the discussion, consent, orders, and onward referrals at the
end of the consult. This segment owns everything between the RT plan
and the closing line of the letter.

Fields:
- discussion_summary: 1–3 sentences on what was discussed with the
  patient (prognosis, treatment options, role of RT). Use the
  standard phrasing pattern but anchor to actual content of the
  encounter.
- patient_understanding_and_consent: 1–2 sentences confirming the
  patient verbalised understanding and agreed to proceed (or did
  not, if that was the case).
- simulation_status: e.g., "Simulation booked.",
  "Simulation scheduled for 22-04-2026.", or "" if not discussed.
- orders: list of investigations / procedures / appointments the
  doctor explicitly ORDERED at this visit. Use [] if none. Only
  definitive orders — no conditional items.
  Examples: "Dental clearance prior to RT.", "Repeat MRI pelvis.",
            "DVT prophylaxis assessment."
- onward_referrals: list of specialty referrals the doctor is
  initiating from THIS consult. Each as one string with specialty +
  reason if stated.
  Examples: "Medical oncology — for concurrent chemo planning.",
            "Surgical oncology consultation.",
            "Palliative care — for symptom control."
- advice: list of conditional / future / non-immediate items
  (e.g., "May consider brachytherapy boost depending on response.",
   "Follow-up review in radiation review clinic weekly during RT.").
  Use [] if none.

Rules:
- ✅ Conditional / tentative items belong in `advice`, never in
  `orders`.
- ✅ Use [] for empty lists.
- ❌ Do NOT include toxicity counseling — that belongs to
  SITE_TOXICITY_PROFILE.
- ❌ Do NOT echo dose / fractions / intent here — those belong to
  IMPRESSION_AND_PLAN.
- ❌ Do NOT inject the patient''s name into narrative fields. Use
  "the patient".

