### 12. MENTAL STATUS EXAMINATION

**Description:** Comprehensive Mental Status Examination (MSE) capturing the objective clinical state of the patient during the interview.

**Extraction Rules:**
- **Appearance and Behavior:** Grooming, hygiene, eye contact, psychomotor activity (agitation/retardation), rapport, attitude toward examiner
- **Speech:** Rate (fast/slow/normal), volume, tone, fluency, reaction time
- **Mood and Affect:** Subjective mood in patient''s own words AND objective affect (range, appropriateness, congruency with thought)
- **Thought Process and Content:** Form (tangentiality, flight of ideas, loosening of associations) AND content (delusions, suicidal/homicidal ideation, obsessions, overvalued ideas)
- **Perception:** Hallucinations (auditory/visual/olfactory/tactile) or illusions - type, content, frequency
- **Cognition:** Orientation (time/place/person), attention and concentration, memory (recent/remote)
- **Insight and Judgment:** Grade of insight (Grade 1-6), test judgment and social judgment
- Write "Not elicited" or "Normal" if transcript implies no abnormalities but does not state explicitly
- [NO] Do NOT fabricate findings not stated or implied

**Example:**
{
  "appearance_and_behavior": "Adequately groomed, cooperative, maintained eye contact, no psychomotor agitation or retardation",
  "speech": "Normal rate, volume, and tone. No pressure of speech.",
  "mood_and_affect": "Subjective: ''feeling very low''. Objective: Depressed affect, restricted range, mood-congruent",
  "thought_process_and_content": "Logical and coherent. Content: Hopelessness, worthlessness. No delusions. Passive suicidal ideation present.",
  "perception": "No hallucinations or illusions reported",
  "cognition": "Oriented to time, place, and person. Attention mildly impaired. Recent memory intact.",
  "insight_and_judgment": "Grade 4 insight - aware of illness and need for treatment. Judgment intact."
}

