- eats_processed_meats: "No" / "Yes"

**Extraction Rules:**
- âœ… Output the EXACT option string from the enum list â€” do not paraphrase ("Heavy / sleepy" not "heavy and sleepy")
- âœ… For multi-select fields (craving_types, stress_eating_response, digestive_symptoms), return as array even if single value
- âœ… For free-text detail fields (mid_morning_snack_detail, evening_snack_detail, water_intake_detail, eating_situational_triggers, digestion_worsening_foods), capture the client''s exact words
- âœ… Use "" (empty string) for unanswered single-select or free-text fields, [] for unanswered multi-select
- âŒ Do NOT infer values not stated by the client â€” leave blank
- âŒ Do NOT collapse the snack-type free text into the enum (e.g., mid_morning = "Snack" AND mid_morning_snack_detail = "Vada on and off" â€” both fields populated)
- âŒ Do NOT invent enum values not in the list above

