### 14. TOXICITY FOR RADIOLOGY

Build the early- and late-toxicity sections for the consult letter.
Hybrid segment: render the LIBRARY verbatim and augment with anything
the doctor specifically discussed.

Instructions:

1. SHORTCUT DETECTION — when the doctor invokes ANY of these phrasings,
   treat it as a BINDING instruction to emit ALL applicable library items
   verbatim (do NOT skip, do NOT summarise, do NOT replace with a generic
   sentence):
   - "follow the standard <site> RT toxicity plan"
   - "follow the standard <site> toxicity boilerplate"
   - "apply the standard <site> consent block"
   - "apply the standard <site> radiation toxicity boilerplate"
   - "kindly follow the standard <site> RT toxicity plan"
   - "follow the standard palliative <site> RT toxicity plan"
   - "follow the standard pelvic re-irradiation toxicity plan"
   - similar variations naming the site (breast, prostate, head and
     neck / HN, cervix, vulvar, rectum, palliative spine, whole-brain,
     re-irradiation)
   "Applicable" means: every unconditional library row PLUS every
   conditional row whose trigger is met for this encounter (see rule 3).

2. DEFAULT INCLUSION — even without a shortcut phrase, include EVERY
   unconditional item from `early_toxicity_library` and
   `late_toxicity_library` by default. Render `text` VERBATIM. Set
   `library_id` to the matching `id`.

3. CONDITIONAL ITEMS — each library entry may carry a
   `conditional_trigger` field (e.g. "BRACHYTHERAPY", "SCF", "LEFT_HEART").
   Include such items ONLY when the trigger is satisfied by the
   encounter:
   - `BRACHYTHERAPY` — doctor mentioned brachytherapy / intracavitary /
                       interstitial / applicator / HDR brachy /
                       MR-guided brachy.
   - `SCF`           — doctor mentioned supraclavicular field / SCF
                       irradiation / IMC irradiation / nodal coverage
                       above the axilla / chest wall + nodes.
   - `LEFT_HEART`    — RT is left-sided breast/chest-wall OR doctor
                       mentioned cardiac dose / cardiac risk /
                       deep-inspiration breath-hold (DIBH).
   If the trigger field is absent on a row, the row is unconditional —
   include per rule 2.
   If the trigger field is set but the trigger is NOT satisfied,
   exclude the row entirely.
   (Legacy id-prefix conventions GY_BR_*, BR_SCF_*, BR_LH_* still hold
   as a tie-breaker if a row''''s `conditional_trigger` is missing.)

4. EXPLICIT EXCLUSION — exclude any other (otherwise-included) library
   item ONLY if the doctor explicitly disclaimed it for this patient
   ("we are sparing the rectum, so expect minimal bowel issues" —
   exclude bowel items only if the disclaimer is unambiguous).

5. ADDITIONS — ADD any toxicity the doctor specifically discussed that
   is NOT in the library. For added items, set `library_id` to "" and
   write the text in the same clinical voice as library items.

LIBRARY:
