Examples (cross-site, illustrative):

 - Script 1.1 Breast adjuvant whole-breast, doctor says "kindly follow
   the standard breast RT toxicity plan", right-sided, no SCF/IMC
   coverage
   → include all BR early + late items VERBATIM; EXCLUDE BR_SCF_* and
     BR_LH_* (triggers not met). Result: 4 early + 5 late items.

 - Script 1.2 Breast PMRT post-MRM with SCF + IMC, doctor says "apply
   the standard breast RT toxicity boilerplate, but please flag the
   lymphedema piece prominently"
   → include all BR early + late items + BR_SCF_E01 + BR_SCF_L01 +
     BR_SCF_L02 (SCF trigger met). Right-sided so EXCLUDE BR_LH_*.
     ADD a doctor-specific item emphasising lymphedema if the
     existing BR_E03 / BR_L02 don''''t already cover it.

 - Script 1.3 Breast palliative — left L3 spine 8 Gy/1#, also WBRT
   20 Gy/5# for brain mets. Doctor says "follow the standard
   palliative spine RT toxicity plan" AND "follow the standard
   whole-brain RT toxicity plan — make sure the alopecia, fatigue,
   and memory effects discussion is in there"
   → emit ALL applicable library items for both palliative spine and
     WBRT; if the library covers them under generic palliative codes,
     include those; ADD doctor-specific items for alopecia / memory
     effects if not already in library.

 - Script 2.1 Gyn cervix definitive CRT + brachy. Doctor says "apply
   the standard cervix CRT and brachytherapy toxicity boilerplate"
   → include all GY early + late items AND ALL GY_BR_* items
     (BRACHYTHERAPY trigger met by "brachy").

 - Script 2.2 Gyn endometrial post-op, vault brachy ALONE. Doctor
   says "apply the standard vaginal brachytherapy toxicity discussion
   only — vaginal dryness, stenosis, mild urinary or rectal
   irritation". Earlier the doctor said "the full pelvic EBRT toxicity
   discussion in the template is not applicable in her case".
   → BRACHYTHERAPY trigger MET → include GY_BR_* items.
   → EBRT items explicitly disclaimed → EXCLUDE GY early + late
     unconditionals (per rule 4).

 - Script 2.3 Gyn vulvar palliative. Doctor says "the brachytherapy
   paragraph in the template is not applicable for her — we''''re not
   doing brachy at all in this case. Skip that section entirely."
   AND "follow the standard pelvic palliative RT toxicity boilerplate,
   but please emphasise skin desquamation in the groins and perineum
   given the fields, infection risk on the already-ulcerated mucosa"
   → BRACHYTHERAPY trigger NOT met → EXCLUDE all GY_BR_* items.
   → include all GY early + late unconditionals.
   → ADD doctor-specific items emphasising perineal skin desquamation
     and infection risk if not already in library.

 - Script 3.1 HN post-op adjuvant CRT. Doctor says "follow the
   standard head and neck adjuvant CRT toxicity plan — mucositis,
   dysphagia, xerostomia, skin reactions, taste changes, possible
   feeding tube, plus the late effects discussion including chronic
   dysphagia, neck fibrosis, second malignancy risk"
   → include ALL HN early + late library items VERBATIM. ADD a
     doctor-specific item for "possible PEG / feeding tube" if not
     already in library.

 - Script 4.1 Prostate definitive EBRT + 6mo ADT. Doctor says "apply
   the standard prostate consent and toxicity block from the
   template"
   → include ALL PR early + late library items VERBATIM (covers
     urinary, bowel, ED, < 1% serious side effect line, etc.).

 - Script 4.2 Prostate high-risk pelvic RT + brachy boost. Doctor
   says "apply the standard prostate radiation toxicity boilerplate
   — but please flag explicitly that pelvic nodal RT increases the
   risk of bowel toxicity and lower-limb lymphedema beyond
   prostate-only treatment, and the brachy boost adds urinary
   stricture and retention risk on top"
   → include ALL PR early + late library items VERBATIM. ADD
     doctor-specific items: pelvic-nodal bowel toxicity + lymphedema
     emphasis, brachy-boost urinary stricture / retention.

 - Script 5.1 Rectum long-course CRT. Doctor says "follow the
   standard rectal CRT toxicity plan — acute fatigue, perineal skin
   reactions, cystitis, proctitis, diarrhoea, marrow suppression with
   concurrent chemo, late risk of bowel function changes, sexual
   dysfunction including ED"
   → include ALL RC early + late library items VERBATIM (early covers
     fatigue, perineal skin, cystitis, proctitis, diarrhoea, marrow
     suppression; late covers chronic bowel, sexual dysfunction, etc.).

 - Script 5.3 Rectum re-irradiation. Doctor says "follow the
   standard pelvic re-irradiation toxicity plan, emphasising the
   elevated risk of sacral insufficiency fracture, sacral nerve
   neuropathy, fistula formation, bowel and urinary toxicity given
   the prior RT"
   → include ALL RC early + late library items VERBATIM. ADD
     doctor-specific items emphasising sacral insufficiency fracture,
     sacral nerve neuropathy, fistula formation given prior RT.

Rules:
- ✅ Render included library items VERBATIM (do not paraphrase library
  text).
- ✅ Use [] for early or late only when ALL items are excluded (rare —
  almost always there is at least one unconditional row to include).
- ❌ Do NOT include conditional items (BRACHYTHERAPY / SCF /
  LEFT_HEART) unless their trigger is met for this encounter.
- ❌ Do NOT skip library items just because the doctor used a shortcut
  phrase — the shortcut MEANS "include them all".
- ❌ Do NOT add toxicities from general medical knowledge that the
  doctor did not mention.

Output strictly the JSON schema below.

