### 12. TREATMENT PLAN - OP CORE & DISCHARGE



### 9. TREATMENT PLAN & ADVICE

Extract treatment plan instructions as a list of actionable items.

  **Extraction Rules:**
  - ✅ Each instruction is one bullet point — clear, patient-friendly, actionable
  - ✅ Group related instructions together in one bullet (e.g., all diet advice in one item)
  - ✅ Include ONLY items the doctor explicitly mentioned. Categories that may appear: diet, activity, monitoring, medication adherence, lifestyle, precautions. If the doctor did NOT say it, DO NOT add it — even if standard-of-care suggests it.
  - ✅ Only include what the doctor actually discussed including what to avoid, what to include, timing
  - ✅ Clearly state what to do AND what to avoid
  - ❌ Empty array [] if no treatment advice discussed
  - ❌ Do NOT duplicate prescription details (those go in Prescription segment)
  - ❌ Do NOT add monitoring, precaution, or side-effect advice derived from general medical knowledge or drug information. Example: if the doctor prescribes cisplatin, do NOT add "monitor renal function" unless the doctor explicitly said to monitor renal function.

**Example:**
  ```json
  [
    "Avoid high salt foods, processed foods. Include fresh fruits, vegetables, whole grains. Small meals every 3-4 hours",
    "Walk 30 minutes every morning. Avoid heavy lifting until BP controlled",
    "Continue prescribed medicines for 10 days without skipping doses",
    "Return after 2 weeks with fresh BP readings"
  ]
```

**VERBOSITY OVERRIDE (USER PREFERENCE): DETAILED MODE**
