### 20. PAST HISTORY

**Description:** Capture the patient''s past medical conditions in the fixed checkbox format used on the Bewell OP case sheet â€” HT, DM, Asthma, IHD, Kidney disease â€” plus a `nil` flag, `others` for additional conditions, and a `details` field for elaboration when the doctor or patient provides context (duration, control status, current treatment, etc.).

**Extraction Rules:**
- âœ… Each named condition (`hypertension`, `diabetes_mellitus`, `asthma`, `ihd`, `kidney_disease`) is one of: "Y", "N", or "" (empty if not discussed at all)
- âœ… Mark "Y" if the patient confirms, the doctor states it, or it is clearly documented in past records referenced during the consult
- âœ… Mark "N" only if explicitly denied (e.g., doctor asks "any diabetes?" and patient says "no")
- âœ… Use "" (empty) if the condition was never brought up during the consult â€” do NOT default to "N"
- âœ… `nil` = "Y" ONLY if the patient/doctor explicitly states no past medical history of any kind (e.g., "no comorbidities", "patient is otherwise healthy"). Otherwise "" or "N"
- âœ… `others` â€” free text for any past conditions NOT in the fixed list (e.g., "Hypothyroidism, CVA in 2019, Hepatitis B"). Empty string if none
- âœ… `details` â€” free text elaboration on ANY of the conditions marked "Y" â€” duration, control status, current treatment, complications, etc. Example: "DM for 10 years on Metformin 500mg BD, HbA1c last checked 7.8%. HT for 5 years on Amlodipine, fairly controlled."
- âŒ Do NOT duplicate current medications here â€” those belong in HISTORY.current_medications
- âŒ Do NOT infer "Y" for a condition just because a related medication is being taken â€” only mark "Y" if the condition itself is stated or confirmed

**Example:**
```json
{
  "nil": "",
  "hypertension": "Y",
  "diabetes_mellitus": "Y",
  "asthma": "N",
  "ihd": "",
  "kidney_disease": "N",
  "others": "Hypothyroidism since 2018",
  "details": "DM for 10 years, on Metformin 500mg BD, last HbA1c 7.8%. HT for 5 years on Amlodipine 5mg OD, BP fairly controlled. Hypothyroidism on Thyronorm 50mcg."
}
```

