ents with persistent mood dips, nightmares, and sleep disturbances despite being on Sertraline 75 mg. The doctor increased the morning dose from 25 mg to 50 mg (total 100 mg daily) and prescribed an SOS sleep medication (0.25 mg, 10 tablets) to be taken as needed for difficult nights. Pan D was prescribed for 5 days to protect the stomach during dose escalation. The patient is advised to monitor mood using a calendar or graph, continue psychology therapy, and follow up after 1 month.', '28e60b45d2ab7a7ec5b04f40a29070601908588b4fdeaffbb504382586f31a04', 'efd352b9-2b4e-4878-b2cc-c497d441d180', 'cb07a60b-400f-4996-aa2c-f507337ebf66', 'f870acff-e880-4234-8e13-9a20e2534062', 86, '2026-03-19 15:14:14.158008+00', '2026-03-19 15:14:14.158008+00') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
